OL,3,CPSNI takes action against 74 officers
OL,4,Cover accessing body-worn camera footage
OL,6,FHugh Hume, chief executive of the
OL,7,FPolice Ombudsman's Office, said the
OL,8,Ffootage was viewed for entertainment,
OL,9,Fbut those who did so "showed little
OL,10,Fregard for the privacy of the man
OL,11,Fbeing arrested, nor for the emotional
OL,12,Fwellbeing of their colleague featured
OL,13,Fin the video".
OL,15,F"The responses received from officers,
OL,16,Fwhen asked to provide their reasons
OL,17,Ffor accessing the video, suggested an
OL,18,Fapparent lack of awareness that doing
OL,19,Fso might constitute a criminal or
OL,20,Fmisconduct offence," he said.
